{"body": "Docs look really good to me. I'd just ask you to check the hashes to keep a consistency with spaces:\n\n```ruby\n# The example is like this\nUser.joins(:posts).where({\"posts.published\" => true})\nUser.joins(:posts).where({ :posts => { :published => true } })\n\n# We could use spaces in all hash examples to keep consistency and readability\nUser.joins(:posts).where({ \"posts.published\" => true })\nUser.joins(:posts).where({ :posts => { :published => true } })\n```\n\nThank you!\n/cc @vijaydev ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6319472", "created_at": "2012-06-14T03:12:39Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6697#issuecomment-6319472", "updated_at": "2012-06-14T03:12:39Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6697, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523e301fbd354364b900e38c"}, "id":